Description: inSolutions is an Information Technology Consulting Company.
Headquarters Regions: Greater Atlanta Area, East Coast, Southern US
Full Description: Founded in 1992 during the internet explosion of the early 90’s, inSolutions began as a as a software development company with the goal of building data-centric, secure applications for the web. Through an initial partnership with the American Real Estate Association, inSolutions delivered one of the first database-driven, online property listing services of its time. The new listing service was piloted in Maryland, Virginia and the District of Columbia and provided the initial momentum that would fuel the growth of the online real estate market for the next 25 years. In 1995, inSolutions was contracted by the Department of Defense to assist with the dissemination of “unclassified, but limited” information to their contractors around the globe. The requirements would highlight the need for robust application and data security, along with a new approach for the web. The resulting solution was unveiled at the Pentagon and became one of the first applications at the DoD that leveraged web-based authentication, role-based access control, SSL and proprietary data encryption as the foundation for a comprehensive, secure, document delivery infrastructure for multiple defense organizations.

Description: babberly is a free location-based social application designed to connect people and help them share information instantaneously.
Headquarters Regions: San Francisco Bay Area, Silicon Valley, West Coast
Full Description: Local search is broken, and it sucks. “Likes” and “check-ins” give users and businesses little information, and, in most cases, the data isn’t valid. babberly fixes this by tying in Facebook comments, Twitter tweets, and local babberly conversations including local merchant offers. Compelling conversation is babberly’s key ingredient. babberly aims to become the local search layer on mobile, allowing users to find relevant local search information from like-minded locals. babberly’s platform capitalizes on this by connecting merchants to specific customers who are nearby and soon in-store (via the babberly beacon). Merchants can answer questions in real-time and – most importantly – offer real-time exclusive deals. At any given point, merchants can receive in-depth reports with detailed analytics outlining offer redemptions, check-ins and area activity. A robust backend that aggregates social conversations that are relevant to a user's local search. babberly takes the millions of social conversations occurring on Facebook, Twitter and its own social conversation platform, slices and dices them and provides a relative search result for your local search query. On the merchant side, businesses are able to engage locals by creating real-time offers that are matched to user's search result. In the next version of our merchant platform we leverage a user's precise location within a store, and allow the retailer to deliver highly relevant and compelling content that engages and influences purchase decisions.
Industry Groups: Internet Services, Media and Entertainment, Mobile, Sales and Marketing

Full Description: Dallas plastic surgeon Mark Deuber has more than a decade of experience performing breast augmentation surgery. He has remained up-to-date on the many exciting developments that have taken place in the field of breast enlargement surgery over the past several years, including:  Improved Implants: Breast implants look and feel more natural than ever before. Breast implants come in a range of filler types, sizes, and shapes. Dr. Deuber will work with each patient to select an implant the complements her body and goals. Improved Surgical Techniques: Advanced breast augmentation surgical techniques offer many benefits to patients. First, the recovery period after surgery is much more comfortable. Dr. Deuber employs techniques that reduce trauma to surrounding tissue, resulting in less pain after surgery and a shorter recovery time. Second, new surgical techniques minimize the appearance of scarring after surgery. Incisions made around the areola and in the armpit leave little scarring after surgery. Inframammary incisions can be reduced with the placement of saline implants, which can be filled after they are inserted in the breasts.
